    "Why are they all low paying?",
    "These questions might arise if the individual stops to reflect critically on what they experience, which is rarely the case.",
    "More often than not, the individual just accepts (or has to accept) their experience, without further interrogation.",
    "In the case of the flawed health-care algorithm discussed above, it was not the patients themselves who raised the alarm about the unfair treatment.",
    "Instead, it was a group of scientists running routine statistical checks on healthcare data provided by a large hospital, who came across the disparities."
